{"metadata": {"team_id": "apparent", "run_id": "apparent-defendant", "topic_id": "1009"}, "responses": [{"text": "Saharan dust reaches Florida and Gulf Coast, traveling over 4,000 miles.", "citations": ["976e5a88-b9d0-4613-be71-b666fa22d6f3_776351012", "e7e6c73b-66b8-4b4f-a199-55f37a56213e_528784020"]}, {"text": "Dust reaches Texas, including Houston, San Antonio, Dallas, and South Texas.", "citations": ["958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541", "97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373", "5dc9163b-9ad8-4a82-8d61-269b3aa8f216_79048364", "e7e6c73b-66b8-4b4f-a199-55f37a56213e_528784020"]}, {"text": "Dust reduces atmospheric moisture by ~50%, decreasing cloud formation, precipitation, and tropical cyclone activity.", "citations": ["976e5a88-b9d0-4613-be71-b666fa22d6f3_776351012"]}, {"text": "Dust suppresses hurricanes during Atlantic hurricane season.", "citations": ["976e5a88-b9d0-4613-be71-b666fa22d6f3_776351012", "847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659"]}, {"text": "Dust enhances sunrise and sunset colors, producing dramatic sunsets.", "citations": ["976e5a88-b9d0-4613-be71-b666fa22d6f3_776351012", "5dc9163b-9ad8-4a82-8d61-269b3aa8f216_79048364", "e7e6c73b-66b8-4b4f-a199-55f37a56213e_528784020", "847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659"]}, {"text": "Dust carries nutrients like phosphorus and iron, fertilizing Amazon rainforest and Caribbean Sea ecosystems.", "citations": ["958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541", "97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373", "847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659"]}, {"text": "Dust stimulates phytoplankton growth, boosting marine productivity and fish populations.", "citations": ["958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541", "97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373"]}, {"text": "Dust reflects sunlight, cooling Earth's surface and offsetting some greenhouse warming.", "citations": ["958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541", "97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373", "e7e6c73b-66b8-4b4f-a199-55f37a56213e_528784020"]}, {"text": "Excessive dust smothers coral reefs, blocking sunlight and causing bleaching and biodiversity loss.", "citations": ["958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541", "97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373"]}, {"text": "Dust carries bacteria, fungi, pathogens, and pollutants, raising respiratory and allergy risks.", "citations": ["958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541", "97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373"]}, {"text": "Dust increases respiratory issues, allergies, asthma, COPD, and wheezing.", "citations": ["54c42d43-5691-4a18-a63f-3c936ecb10cc_86116201", "97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373", "5dc9163b-9ad8-4a82-8d61-269b3aa8f216_79048364"]}, {"text": "Dust causes asthma incidence to rise 17-fold in Barbados.", "citations": ["54c42d43-5691-4a18-a63f-3c936ecb10cc_86116201"]}, {"text": "Dust can worsen chronic lung diseases and cause cardiovascular inflammation.", "citations": ["54c42d43-5691-4a18-a63f-3c936ecb10cc_86116201"]}, {"text": "Dust can trigger minor allergy-like symptoms and reduce visibility.", "citations": ["847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659"]}, {"text": "Dust causes hazy skies and milky afternoons.", "citations": ["5dc9163b-9ad8-4a82-8d61-269b3aa8f216_79048364"]}, {"text": "Dust peaks late June to mid-August, overlapping Atlantic hurricane season.", "citations": ["5dc9163b-9ad8-4a82-8d61-269b3aa8f216_79048364"]}, {"text": "Mitigation requires global health monitoring, preparedness plans, and air quality management during dust events.", "citations": ["958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541"]}, {"text": "Communities along dust columns need monitoring and health preparedness.", "citations": ["97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373"]}, {"text": "Trinidad has a dust warning system providing air quality alerts.", "citations": ["54c42d43-5691-4a18-a63f-3c936ecb10cc_86116201"]}, {"text": "Stay indoors, avoid outdoor activity,