{"metadata": {"team_id": "apparent", "run_id": "apparent-defendant", "topic_id": "1029"}, "responses": [{"text": "Mary Shelley\u2019s Frankenstein (1818) is the first modern science\u2011fiction novel.", "citations": ["8dffe6e3-b2e0-4574-97ae-d3a72b383e10_533797018", "313a3381-4790-45a2-8734-d595fd2ee46a_38674691"]}, {"text": "H.G. Wells\u2019s Time Machine (1895) pioneered travel and alien invasion tropes.", "citations": ["8dffe6e3-b2e0-4574-97ae-d3a72b383e10_533797018", "313a3381-4790-45a2-8734-d595fd2ee46a_38674691", "764901a5-ae9e-4bb0-be99-00e9fcaa1a8b_389925305"]}, {"text": "Jules Verne\u2019s 1863 story Five Weeks in a Balloon introduced early speculative adventure.", "citations": ["764901a5-ae9e-4bb0-be99-00e9fcaa1a8b_389925305"]}, {"text": "20th\u2011century sci\u2011fi explored capitalism, communism, nuclear threats, racism, and pollution.", "citations": ["01c44cda-9c26-4674-815e-de91cca921c4_209737677"]}, {"text": "Late 20th/early 21st\u2011century sci\u2011fi shifted to ecological crises, transhumanism, and AI.", "citations": ["01c44cda-9c26-4674-815e-de91cca921c4_209737677"]}, {"text": "Contemporary sci\u2011fi increasingly focuses on gender identity, trans identity, and intersectionality.", "citations": ["774699db-8b63-4839-8211-2760098d90ac_1033840002", "8b0ef215-1d52-43a4-9ba0-15215b7f661c_150233956", "01c44cda-9c26-4674-815e-de91cca921c4_209737677"]}, {"text": "Women authors like Winterson, Jemisin, Butler, Jones, and Russell shape modern sci\u2011fi.", "citations": ["774699db-8b63-4839-8211-2760098d90ac_1033840002", "8dffe6e3-b2e0-4574-97ae-d3a72b383e10_533797018", "313a3381-4790-45a2-8734-d595fd2ee46a_38674691", "b189e16e-b1b0-4531-898b-22bc44ca457e_717111571", "e0d0eaca-aa98-46fb-ab70-0f03363ebcea_816797857"]}, {"text": "Authors of color such as Okorafor, Liu, El\u202fSayed, Jemisin, and Wells gain prominence.", "citations": ["b189e16e-b1b0-4531-898b-22bc44ca457e_717111571", "8dffe6e3-b2e0-4574-97ae-d3a72b383e10_533797018", "e0d0eaca-aa98-46fb-ab70-0f03363ebcea_816797857"]}, {"text": "Lack of diversity in sci\u2011fi films limits imagination of future with people of color.", "citations": ["8b4f4c1e-487c-4250-846e-31739ce65460_1048251213"]}, {"text": "Snowpiercer features racially diverse characters and reflects contemporary world in its future setting.", "citations": ["8b4f4c1e-487c-4250-846e-31739ce65460_1048251213"]}, {"text": "Saudi Arabia\u2019s first sci\u2011fi conference highlighted women pioneers and 30\u2011year progress.", "citations": ["521ac676-eb0a-4808-8618-33cf0a1f7330_242685488"]}, {"text": "Arabic sci\u2011fi roots trace to medieval philosophers Ibn\u202fSina, Ibn\u202fTufail, and Ibn\u202fNafis.", "citations": ["764901a5-ae9e-4bb0-be99-00e9fcaa1a8b_389925305"]}, {"text": "Modern Arabic sci\u2011fi includes Tawfiq al\u2011Hakim\u2019s In a Million Years and Journey to the Future.", "citations": ["764901a5-ae9e-4bb0-be99-00e9fcaa1a8b_389925305"]}, {"text": "Arab world\u2019s sci\u2011fi market grew 400% post\u2011COVID, with 8,000 Arabic titles.", "citations": ["521ac676-eb0a-4808-8618-33cf0a1f7330_242685488"]}, {"text": "Speculative fiction expanded into comics, video games, and choose\u2011your\u2011own adventures, influenced by Marvel.", "citations": ["dc3c3b72-0d32-4b24-827d-e46b2f82f7cd_304953587"]}, {"text": "Interdisciplinary collaboration between authors and scientists is emphasized in the Dartmouth Speculative Fiction Project.", "citations": ["dc3c3b72-0d32-4b24-827d-e46b2f82f7cd_304953587"]}, {"text": "Short\u2011fiction sci\u2011fi is in a golden age, with Nebula, Hugo, and Locus finalists.", "citations": ["b189e16e-b1b0-4531-898b-22bc44ca457e_717111571"]}, {"text": "Tech\u2011based fiction reflects real\u2011world tech scandals and societal fears, gaining popularity during Trump era.", "citations": ["7e419fc1-0a90-48de-90ec-e777cf646241_187716990"]}, {"text": "Adaptations of sci\u2011fi works like Dune, Foundation, and Binti broaden audience reach.", "citations": ["8dffe6e3-b2e0-